Saudi-led air strikes on a school in a rebel-held province of northern Yemen have killed 10 children and wounded 28 others, Doctors Without Borders (MSF) said on Sunday.&#8220;We received 10 dead children and 28 wounded, all under the age of 15, who are victims of air strikes on a Koranic school in Haydan,&#8221; in Saada province, said MSF spokeswoman Malak Shaher, adding the attack took place on Saturday.-AFP